<subSubSection id="A6FE6576FF915057FDDE76319253FCBE" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EE5B36FDFF915057FDDE763196E0FE36" blockId="11.[144,243,367,391]" box="[144,243,367,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FDDE763196E0FE36" box="[144,243,367,391]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE5B36FDFF915057FDDE76C99253FCBE" blockId="11.[144,1104,407,783]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FF0E76C99519FE1E" author="Richardson H" box="[576,778,407,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref7311" refString="Richardson H. 1904. Contributions to the Natural History of the Isopoda. Proc US Natl Mus. 27: 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="1904">Richardson (1904)</bibRefCitation>
from a single mature pair collected off Port Otway, Chilean Patagonia. 
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FF3876E99243FE7E" author="Miranda-Vargas P &amp; Roccatagliata D" box="[630,1104,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref6888" refString="Miranda-Vargas P, Roccatagliata D. 2004. A redescription and new host record for the parasitic isopod Pseudione tuberculata (Epicaridea: Bopyridae) from the Beagle Channel, Argentina. Cah Biol Mar. 45: 157 - 166" type="journal article" year="2004">Miranda-Vargas and Roccatagliata (2004)</bibRefCitation>
subsequently published a detailed redescription of both sexes based on several specimens collected from two different hosts from Argentinean Patagonia. 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FE2C76A99243FDBE" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1904" box="[866,1104,503,527]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Pseudione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FE2C76A99243FDBE" box="[866,1104,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">Pseudione tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
parasitizes three lithodid hosts (see 
<tableCitation id="A3660346FF915057FF5F75499472FD9E" box="[529,609,535,559]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[58,116,459,481]" captionText="Table 1. List of all known species of bopyrids from the west coast of South America with hosts, zoogeographical ranges, and vertical distributions." pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">Table 1</tableCitation>
) from Patagonian austral waters. The prevalence of 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FDA475699791FDFE" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1904" box="[234,386,567,591]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Pseudione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FDA475699791FDFE" box="[234,386,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">P. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FCEA75699493FDFE" box="[420,640,567,591]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FCEA75699493FDFE" box="[420,640,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">Paralomis granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can reach nearly 46% in hosts of carapace length of 
<quantity id="291C9B18FF915057FDB675099792FDDE" box="[248,385,599,623]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4949999999999999" metricValueMax="1.9899999999999998" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" unit="mm" value="14.95" valueMax="19.9" valueMin="10.0">10–19.9 mm</quantity>
, but this rate steeply declines as host size increases (
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FEF975099746FD3E" author="Roccatagliata D &amp; Lovrich GA" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="720 - 729" refId="ref7368" refString="Roccatagliata D, Lovrich GA. 1999. Infestation of the false king crab Paralomis granulosa (Decapoda: Lithodidae) by Pseudione tuberculata (Isopoda: Bopyridae) in the Beagle Channel, Argentina. J Crust Biol. 19: 720 - 729." type="journal article" year="1999">Roccatagliata and Lovrich 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FC2875299429FD3E" author="Canete JI &amp; Cardenas A &amp; Oyarzun S &amp; Plana J &amp; Palacios M &amp; Santana M" box="[358,570,631,655]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="265 - 274" refId="ref6435" refString="Canete JI, Cardenas A, Oyarzun S, Plana J, Palacios M, Santana M. 2008. Pseudione tuberculata Richardson, 1904 (Isopoda: Bopyridae): a parasite of juveniles of the king crab Lithodes santolla (Molina, 1782) (Anomura: Lithodidae) in the Magellan Strait, Chile. Rev Biol Mar Oceanogr. 43 (2): 265 - 274" type="journal article" year="2008">Cañete et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
reported high prevalence (near 30%) of 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FEBF752996C1FD1E" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1904" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Pseudione" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FEBF752996C1FD1E" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">P. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from juveniles of 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FCE775C99444FD1E" box="[425,599,663,687]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Lithodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satolla">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FCE775C99444FD1E" box="[425,599,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">Lithodes satolla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Magellan region. Detrimental effects reported for 
<taxonomicName id="29E44D7EFF915057FC6E75E997BAFD7E" box="[288,425,695,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="DC90EAEFFF915057FC6E75E997BAFD7E" box="[288,425,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050">P. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include sterilization and reduction of growth (
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FEF975E99746FD5E" author="Roccatagliata D &amp; Lovrich GA" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="720 - 729" refId="ref7368" refString="Roccatagliata D, Lovrich GA. 1999. Infestation of the false king crab Paralomis granulosa (Decapoda: Lithodidae) by Pseudione tuberculata (Isopoda: Bopyridae) in the Beagle Channel, Argentina. J Crust Biol. 19: 720 - 729." type="journal article" year="1999">Roccatagliata and Lovrich 1999</bibRefCitation>
). High mortality is also suspected in small-sized crabs and evidence of former parasitization in larger hosts has been found (
<bibRefCitation id="8A754B0CFF915057FF9F75A99226FCBE" author="Roccatagliata D &amp; Lovrich GA" box="[721,1077,759,783]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2050" pagination="720 - 729" refId="ref7368" refString="Roccatagliata D, Lovrich GA. 1999. Infestation of the false king crab Paralomis granulosa (Decapoda: Lithodidae) by Pseudione tuberculata (Isopoda: Bopyridae) in the Beagle Channel, Argentina. J Crust Biol. 19: 720 - 729." type="journal article" year="1999">Roccatagliata and Lovrich 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
